text: Osierfield is an unincorporated community in Irwin County, in the U.S. state of Georgia. ==History== A post office was established at Osierfield in 1901, and remained in operation until 1967. The Georgia General Assembly incorporated Osierfield in 1912. The town's municipal charter was repealed in 1995. ==References== Category:Former municipalities in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Unincorporated communities in Irwin County, Georgia Category:Populated places disestablished in 1995
